messages.content: Another issue I encountered this morning (before the error occurred) is that only one Transfer Order is being generated in NAV for the entire load list. When I checked the table, I noticed that the same OrderID is being used for the entire session. Previously, each To Location generated its own OrderID.

Leigh, Sarah - would one of you all be able to look at the actual error log after you get the error and screenshot it so we can see the error there? That will make it easier for the developers to diagnose! After the error if you don’t see anything in there please let me know.
I am getting error now after I hit the updated version
Sarah was able to get by this
Good morning - I am getting an error "Failed to Create Session" testing Restock Load Lists when I select "Routes"

Hey guys,

 

We’re working through the RESTOCK Demand Based Replenishment setup and need a historical sales file with all sales from 2022 through today. This should just use the same layout and format as the current daily POS files we’re receiving. This can be placed on the FTP server like the other files we are getting as well.

 

We only need this for Dan’s station, 035, for now since he’s the only station piloting.

 

Let me know if that makes sense or if anything needs clarification.
Thanks. We can plan on deploying Monday if that works for you
Leigh, we are not going to be able to release tonight. We are still working through issues. I will keep you all updated!
Will update you by 4PM CT with a status update.
Nathan van Wingerden, we will need to coordinate again with Dan and Improving so please let me know once you guys are good to go. We may need to shoot for Monday at this point.
Hey, we added inventory of this item and it isn't showing in inventory in NAV or the app. Any thoughts what may be holding this up?
Yes, they will need to click update! We are still in the middle of testing a fix for the bug discovered yesterday, so release is still TBD pending that.
Will users need to update the app?

It's in the current sprint and should be included in the next release. I just checked, and you're right, its not showing on the priority list, however, from what i can tell it should be showing. I'll see what's going on with it!
